{"sectionId":695,"sectionIdLiteral":"695","humanId":"lesson-278","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"If I am bound, my Father is not free.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 278"},"annotation":"W-278","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-278\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"695#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>If I accept that I am prisoner within a body, in a world in which all things that seem to live appear to die, then is my Father prisoner with me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>And this do I believe, when I maintain the laws the world obeys must I obey; the frailties and the sins which I perceive are real, and cannot be escaped.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>If I am bound in any way, I do not know my Father nor my Self.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And I am lost to all reality.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>For truth is free, and what is bound is not a part of truth.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"695#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, I ask for nothing but the truth.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I have had many foolish thoughts about myself and my creation, and have brought a dream of fear into my mind.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Today, I would not dream.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>I choose the way to You instead of madness and instead of fear.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"695#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>For truth is safe, and only love is sure.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"If I accept that I am prisoner within a body, in a world in which all thi